quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  18,98,"He said, 'This is a mercy from my Lord. Then, when the promise of my Lord will come, He will make it leveled to the ground. And the promise of my Lord is always true.""
  18,99,"And on that day, We will leave them (Ya'juj and Ma'juj) surging over one another. And the Horn shall be blown then We shall gather them together."
  18,100,"And on that day We will bring Jahannam fully exposed before the infidels"
  18,101,"whose eyes were under a cover against My re-minders, and they were not able to listen. ["
  18,102,"Do, then, the disbelievers deem (it fit) that they take My servants as patrons beside Me? Surely, We have pre-pared Jahannam as entertainment for the disbelievers."
  18,103,"Say, "Shall We tell you about the greatest losers in respect of (their) deeds?"
  18,104,"Those are the ones whose effort in the worldly life has gone in vain while they think they are doing well."
  18,105,"Those are the ones who disbelieved in the signs of their Lord and in the meeting with Him, so their deeds have gone waste and We shall not as-sign to them any weight."
  18,106,"That is their punishment, the Jahannam, for they disbelieved and made My signs and My messengers a mockery."
  18,107,"Surely those who believed and did righteous deeds theirs are the Gardens of Firdaus as entertainment"
  18,108,"where they will live forever and will not wish to move from there.""
  18,109,"Say, "If the ocean were to be ink for the Words of my Lord, the ocean would have been consumed before the Words of my Lord are exhausted, even though we were to bring another one, like it, in addition.""
  18,110,"Say, "Surely, I am but a human being like you; it is revealed to me that your God is the One God. So the one who hopes to meet his Lord must do righteous deed and must not associate anyone in the worship of his Lord.""